                         Angular

                    Bank App in Angular

                    Frond end: Angular
                    Back end: Nodejs(Express)
                    DataBase:MongoDb

    Basic Building Blocks

    1 module - To import 3rd party libraries
    2 component - To create html and css files

          Basic commands   

        1.Create a project- ng new project_name
        2.create a component- ng g c component_name
        3.run-ng serve --open   


        1) Data binding

        To share data inside the component

        ts-component and html-view

        1.1)one way data binding  (TS to HTML or HTML to TS file)

         a)component to view
              a.1)string interpolation- syntax - {{expression}}

              a.2)Property binding- syntax - [attribute_name]="property"

          b)view to component
            b.1)event binding - syntax - (event_name)="function_name"
            b.2)Event binding using $Event - syntax - (event_name)="function_name($event)"
            b.3)event binding using template referencing variable - #variable_name

        1.2) two way binding
        data share in both directions(TS to HTML and HTML to TS)  

        ngModel (library) - import from formsmodule

        import ngModel from FormsModule 

        2)Angular Routing 
        To set path for a component

        {
        path:'',component:LoginComponent
       //'' - 4200 login
        },
       {
        path:'dashboard',component:DashboardComponent
      //'' - 4200/dashboard - register
       }
       -use routeroutlet inside the root component


        3) Dependancy injection

        To share data between two components
        -here ew use constructor to achive this concept
        eg-login to dashboard


         4)angular services
         To hold redundant data

         to create service in angular- ng g s service_name

          